Here is a C code that opens a file and prints the value of each bit byte by byte:

```c
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

int main() {
    FILE *f = fopen("file.txt", "rb");
    if (f == NULL) {
        printf("Error opening file");
        exit(1);
    }

    char c;
    while ((c = fgetc(f)) != EOF) {
        for (int i=7; i>=0; i--) {
            printf("%d", (c >> i) & 1);
        }
        printf(" ");
    }
    printf("\n");
    fclose(f);
} 
```

This code:

- Opens the file.txt file in read binary mode 
- Reads each byte from the file using fgetc()
- For each byte, it prints the individual bit values from most significant bit to least significant bit
- It prints a space after each byte and a newline at the end
- Closes the file

So if file.txt contained the bytes 0b00110101 and 0b00001111, the output would be:

1 1 0 1 0 1 0 1 0 0 0 0 1 1 1 1

Here's a simple implementation of a Tic Tac Toe board using HTML and CSS:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Tic Tac Toe</title>
    <style>
        body {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        }
        .board {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 100px);
            grid-template-rows: repeat(3, 100px);
            gap: 5px;
        }
        .cell {
            width: 100px;
            height: 100px;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            font-size: 24px;
            border: 2px solid #000;
            cursor: pointer;
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
        }
        .cell:hover {
            background-color: #e0e0e0;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="board">
        <div class="cell" id="cell1">1</div>
        <div class="cell" id="cell2">2</div>
        <div class="cell" id="cell3">3</div>
        <div class="cell" id="cell4">4</div>
        <div class="cell" id="cell5">5</div>
